--- title: "RMarkdown" execute: freeze: auto error: true warning: true message: true knitr: opts_chunk: collapse: true comment: "#>" --- ## Duplicated headings in table of contents If your document has headings appearing more than once in the wrong place, it might be because of an unclosed tag, like a `
` that doesn't have a corresponding `
`. This is an example of an RMarkdown document which has a broken table of contents (you can see the HTML output [here](broken_toc.html)): ```{.markdown} --- title: "Document" output: html_document: toc: true toc_float: true --- # Header 1
text # Header 2 text ``` This produces a warning message (possibly in the "Background Jobs" tab in RStudio) like this: ```{.bash} [WARNING] Div at tmp.knit.md line 11 column 1 unclosed at tmp.knit.md line 19 column 1, closing implicitly. ```
